sentences: KORR-A reemerged on the music scene in 2013 with her  "Fiyacraka."

Crafted by Grammy-nominated producer, Dave Audé—who has scored over 83 #1 Billboard Dance/Club Play Chart— "Fiyacraka" reached #18 on the Billboard Dance Club Charts, #12 on UK's Music Week Commercial Pop Charts, and #7 on the DJ Times National Dance/Crossover Charts.
In 2015 KORR-A aligned with Tearce "Kizzo," who has worked his sonic magic with everyone from Afrojack and Inna to Jason Derulo, Pitbull (rapper) and Ne-Yo.

She followed up "Swipe Right" with another Kizzo collabo as he helped her add a provocative touch to "C&C Music Factory's 1990 #1 hit "Gonna Make You Sweat (Everybody Dance Now)" on her hit "Everybody Get Down."
